&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Onsite, full-time role with occasional overtime at our Headquarters in Pleasanton, CA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible, results-focused work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean, high-tech manufacturing facility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Small, collaborative team that loves what they do&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong opportunities for growth and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process silica wafers through etching, dicing, cleaning, inspection, assembly, and packaging operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate and monitor specialized manufacturing equipment, including chemical etch systems, wafer dicing equipment, UV curing systems, and inspection tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow SOPs and manufacturing instructions while maintaining product quality, traceability, and accurate production records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform inspections and identify defects in wafers, components, and finished products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely handle chemicals and manufacturing materials in accordance with EHS requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain cleanroom and manufacturing work areas to company standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support troubleshooting, root-cause investigations, and continuous improvement efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively and flexibly to meet production schedules and customer demand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent; college or vocational training preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in semiconductor processing, medical device manufacturing, optics manufacturing, or other precision manufacturing environment preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with laboratory or manufacturing chemical safety practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent manual dexterity and ability to safely handle fragile wafers, glass substrates, and precision-manufactured components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail, organization, and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, learn quickly, and consistently follow detailed procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dependable, adaptable, and motivated to contribute to a fast-paced team environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
